The Federal University of Agriculture, Abeokuta (FUNAAB) students have protested the abduction of their colleague, Toyinbo Olayinka from a farm in the city by unknown gunmen. The protest was held Monday at the schoolâ€™s main gate with students carrying placards with different inscriptions while chanting.  On Saturday, Olayinka, a 400 level student of Aquaculture and Fisheries Management, was kidnapped at Abule-Itoko on the Abeokuta-Ibadan Road in the Odeda Local Government Area of Ogun State. It was learnt that the abductors demanded a ransom of N50 million.



